news.title: China: Longfor Group & Midea Real Estate plan to raise $5 billion in debt
news.para: NAFMII, which has semi-official status under the auspices of China's central bank, said that Longfor had completed the registration for 20 billion yuan worth of debt, while it had accepted an application by Midea to raise 15 billion yuan.

news.title: British Land says low appetite for property purchases hits valuations
news.para: The owner of London office spaces such as Broadgate, Regent's Place and Paddington Central, British Land said valuations of its largest portfolio - office assets - fell 2.7% during the half-year period.

news.title: HDFC Capital selects 10 startups for funding through H@ART platform
news.para: ​H@ART Platform recently announced that it has raised over Rs 500 crore through global investors as the first close of its property technology fund, HDFC said in a statement on Wednesday.

news.title: Kotak Mahindra Bank cuts 1-year MCLR rate by 20 bps, hikes for other tenors
news.para: For other tenor loans ranging from overnight to three year, the revised rates are in the range of 7.80-9.05 per cent, according to Kotak.

news.title: Mumbai: Input tax credit not available to co-operative housing society in respect of repair work
news.para: Mahavir Nagar Shiv Shrushti CHS had constructed a building on a plot allotted by MHADA and was registered under GST. The AAAR held that the CHS itself is not a 'works contract' service provider, nor is it in the business of providing works contract services.

news.title: Paras Buildtech acquires two-acre land for Rs 91 crore from South Indian bank in Noida
news.para: The company plans to develop 2.7 lakh sq ft of retail and about 1.5 lakh sq ft of office space with the total investment of about Rs 450 crore.

news.title: October home registration count highest this year in Kolkata metropolitan area
news.para: The registration of 6,788 residential sales deeds in October 2022 marked a 45% volume growth over October 2021 and a 17% upswing over September 2021.

news.title: Goa: Excessive sand mining sees Mandovi river banks collapse in 12 villages
news.para: The inspection was carried out last month after the chairperson of the village biodiversity management committee of Vere-Vaghurme complained of gross CRZ violation and of excessive sand extraction in the river.

news.title: Karnataka: Environmentalists want construction with burnt bricks stopped
news.para: They have demanded that the government encourage the use of compressed earth blocks and discourage burnt bricks.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM launches housing scheme for construction workers
news.para: The chief minister had made an announcement earlier this year regarding a subsidy of Rs 4 lakh for registered construction workers to build their houses.

news.title: Indore civic body earns Rs 120 crore as building compounding fee
news.para: The state government had on August 10, 2021, made necessary amendments to the Municipal Act to ease the regularization of (illegal) colonies.

news.title: Ludhiana: Residents struggle for NOCs, building plan nod
news.para: The NOCs are required for the sale and purchase of any property, especially in unauthorised colonies, while construction of buildings is prohibited without building plan approval.

news.title: NGT directs Nimawat Granite to pay interim compensation for violating green norms
news.para: ​A bench of chairperson Justice A K Goel noted that the company had filed an application stating it had complied with the environmental norms but the annexed documents did not conclusively show it actually did.

news.title: Goa: Co-working space on four beaches approved, one within turtle centre
news.para: At Miramar, the co-working space will be created near the Manohar Parrikar Samadhi complex, while in the case of Morjim there will be a co-working space cum turtle nesting interpretation centre, as this stretch of the coast in Pernem sees nesting by Olive Ridley turtles.

news.title: SBI hikes MCLR by up to 15 bps across tenors
news.para: The benchmark one-year MCLR, which is used as base for fixing most of home, auto and personal loans, has been raised by 10 basis points (bps) to 8.05 per cent, as against 7.95 per cent earlier.
